    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_696_to-FE_letter01_page01.jpg"/>
               <p>
                   <note>60</note>
                   Odd Replies to <hi rend="underline">odd</hi> questions<lb/>	
                   I asked the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BailX1">Baillies</persName> about the princesses -<lb/>
                   The <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SophG1">princess Sophia</persName> is not insane - only very<lb/>
                   nervous &amp; weak - this is the truth and <hi rend="underline">nervous</hi> is<lb/>
                   <hi rend="underline">not here</hi> used as a soft equivocal word.<lb/>
                   The <persName ref="./Personography.xml#AmelG1">princess Amelia</persName> - was said to have died a martyr<lb/>
                   to the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#GeorG2">Kings</persName> evil &amp; all scars <del>and</del> &amp; sores - absolutely<lb/>
                   false - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BailM1">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Baillie</persName> saw her <add>during all her illness</add> <hi rend="underline">after death</hi> <add><unclear></unclear></add> - told his <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BailJ1">sister</persName><lb/>
                   that her neck &amp; every part of her was free from all<lb/>
                   scar or sore or swelling or any symptom of that<lb/>
                   disease - She died of atrophy - really worn out - anxiety<lb/>
                   of mind accelerating or producing it - all about her<lb/>
                   children true - <add><persName ref="./Personography.xml#FitzC2">Fitzroy</persName></add> Her husband I <hi rend="underline">think</hi> she said but am not<lb/>
                   <hi rend="underline">sure - was not</hi> always kind to her<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                   The <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SophG1">princess</persName> <gap></gap> is married it is believed to<lb/>
                   <persName ref="./Personography.xml#GartT1">Gen<hi rend="superscript">l</hi>. Garth</persName> <del>and as</del> <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BailJ1">Miss Baillie</persName> says you w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi><lb/>
                   <hi rend="underline">be surprised</hi> at her choice if you saw him -<lb/>
                   All the stories about the Kings apartments being<lb/>
                    
                   <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_696_to-FE_letter01_page02.jpg"/>
                   <hi rend="underline">stuffed</hi> to prevent cries being heard <del>is</del> false -<lb/>
                   <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BailM1">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Baillie</persName> says the rooms are just as they always<lb/>
                   were -<lb/></p>
                   <p>
                   As to the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CharL1">Queen</persName> no mortal knows whether she<lb/>
                   will die tomorrow - or live months - All the<lb/>
                   physicians say she may die any hour or<lb/>
                   may hold out a month or 2 -<lb/></p>
                    <p>
                   <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BailM1">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Baillie</persName> never sees her - never has seen<lb/>
                   <hi rend="underline">her since her</hi> illness<lb/></p>
            </div>
